                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Careful</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red.</seg>
                        <persName role="scribe" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS12076ZawaldaMaryam">Zawalda
                           Māryām</persName> is mentioned as the scribe in the concluding
                        supplication formula (<locus target="#108va">108va</locus>, <locus from="14" to="15">14-15</locus>, 20-21).<date>18th century</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; 
 the word mǝʿrāf;
 six lines
                           (both columns) of the incipit page of each text (fols. 3rab, 36rab,
                           54rab, 85rab), divided into three groups, alternating with black
                           lines;
 some lines (1-3) within “short postscript” of the each
                           text;
 two initial lines of the list of “tituli” for the Gospel of
                           John (fol. 108rb [ls. 8-9]);
 some extra notes, indicating the
                           chapter titles, and some of the lines above and below them;
 Ethiopic
                           numerals indicating the “tituli”;
 the horizontal dashes above and
                           below Ethiopic numerals; 
 elements of the punctuation signs;
                           names of the scribe (fol. 108va, ls. 14-15; 20-21) and donors (fol.
                           108va, ls. 8, 9, 10).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
